           <gco:CharacterString>This dataset contains counts, rates, and confidence intervals of heat-related deaths among California residents for the years 2000-2009. These data are stratified by year, age group, race/ethnicity and gender. Crude and age-adjusted rates and confidence intervals are included.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>To provide data on the California Environmental Public Health Tracking Network consistent with the National Environmental Public Health Tracking Network. Heat-related deaths are selected based on cause of death (including underlying and immediate, intermediate, and contributing causes) coding: http://www.ehib.org/page.jsp?page_key=896#heat_classification. The California EPHT Program receives calendar year vital records Multiple Cause of Death files (MCOD) from the state's Center for Health Statistics (CHS). These files were created by the National Center for Health Statistics. Each record may include up to 20 causes of death derived from California death certificates. All causes of death are coded according to the International Classification of Diseases version 10. Further information on the California Center for Health Statistics and their available data is located at: http://www.cdph.ca.gov/data/dataresources/requests/Pages/VitalStatisticsBirthDeathFetalDeathMarriageData.aspx.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:supplementalInformation>       </gmd:MD_DataIdentification>    </gmd:identificationInfo>    <gmd:contentInfo><!-- translated from eainfo to MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription--><gmd:MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription>          <gmd:includedWithDataset>             <gco:Boolean>false</gco:Boolean>          </gmd:includedWithDataset>          <gmd:featureCatalogueCitation gco:nilReason="unknown">             <gmd:CI_Citation>                <gmd:title>                   <gco:CharacterString>Entity and Attribute Information</gco:CharacterString>                </gmd:title>                <gmd:date gco:nilReason="unknown"/>                <gmd:otherCitationDetails>                   <gco:CharacterString>Entity and Attribute Overview: This data contains the following fields: Cnty_FIPS Start_Date End_Date Measure_ID Measure_VA Case counts are aggregated for May-September and calculated by year, age group, race/ethnicity and gender. Each year, CEHTP obtains the MCOD dataset from CHS and creates datasets to be used for public health surveillance while maintaining confidentiality. This dataset on the CEHTP portal includes deaths due to heat for May-September for the years 2000-2009. Each event is identified by looking at cause of death (underlying, intermediate, etc.) based on the International Classification of Disease, Tenth Revision, Clinical Modification (ICD-10-CM). A diagnostic ICD-10-CM code of T67.X or X30 indicates the underlying or contributing cause of death was heat. Counts, rates, and confidence intervals were calculated by age-group, gender, and race/ethnicity.To calculate rates, we use population data from the California Department of Finance (DOF). DOF uses year 2000 population data collected by the U.S. Census Bureau and takes into account survival rates, migration patterns, and fertility rates for California to project the California population by county, race/ethnicity, age, and gender for 2000-2050 (State of California, Department of Finance, Population Projections for California and Its Counties 2000-2050, Sacramento, California, July 2007). Confidence intervals for rates of hospitalizations and ED visits are calculated using the Tiwari, Clegg, and Zou (Methods in Medical Research, 2006; 15:547-569). For more information on how the data is calculated and accompanying limitations, see the methods section: http://www.ehib.org/page.jsp?page_key=896.</gco:CharacterString>
